						<summary>

						<p>On a mutilated Jaina image in the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It contains the names of the <hi rend="italic">Yakshīs,</hi> Aparājitā, Mahāmānasī, Anantamati and Chakrēśvārī and, the <hi rend="italic">Yakshas,</hi> Vṛishabha, Pātāḷa, Kubēra and Śāntinātha of the Jaina pantheon.</p>						

						</summary>
